cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.CR 

The paper discusses the citation impact of scientific publications, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. cs.DL (Digital Libraries) is the most likely category as it deals with the organization, retrieval, and dissemination of digital information, including scientific publications. cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also likely as it deals with the search and retrieval of information from large collections of documents. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is relevant as the paper discusses the impact of publications in different research fields, which can be seen as networks of related topics. cs.CY (Computational Geometry) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are less likely but still possible as they deal with the analysis and measurement of complex systems, which can be applied to the citation impact of publications.
